The use of an attention module and the focus on interpretability could also suggest that the paper belongs to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. 

The paper's focus on image classification and the use of CNNs could also suggest that it belongs to the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category, as CNNs are commonly used in natural language processing tasks such as text classification. 

Finally, the paper's use of an end-to-end pipeline and focus on achieving high accuracy with minimal training time could suggest that it belongs to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
